pageContext.claim: “Nobody has ever seen anybody from our country even negotiate on trade -- trade with China and with other countries.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. The United States has been negotiating with other countries on trade since the dawn of the republic. Trade negotiations have been a key aspect of the U.S.-China relationship. Before he was president, Trump spent years criticizing existing trade deals and campaigned on scrapping or renegotiating several of them.
